Forward Deployment Task: Build a Status Page

Objective:
Design and deploy a production-ready status page for a website or application that monitors uptime, logs incidents, and notifies users of outages in real time.

Task Overview:
Many Generative AI companies prioritize minimizing downtime. Your task is to build a system that reflects this by providing visibility into system health and reliability.

We like Next.js or python as a tech stack, but its all up too you. Please include in your email attachment, your github, personal projects, and this projects public github url.

Requirements:

1. Status Page

* Host your status page at any domain
* It should display:

  * Current system status (e.g. Operational, Degraded, Down)
  * Historical incidents (past 24 hours, you can be creative)
  * Timestamps for all events
  * Brief descriptions of issues
* The interface should be clean and easy to understand

1. Integration

* Your status page should monitor:

  * Your personal website, or
  * [https://paveer.com](https://paveer.com), or
  * Any project of your choice
* You must use incident.io for incident tracking and management

3. GitHub Repository

* Create a public GitHub repository
* Include:

  * All source code
  * Setup instructions (README)
  * Optional: architecture or system design explanation

4. Testing and Incident Logging

* Simulate real failures (e.g. server downtime, API errors)
* Log incidents with:

  * Start time
  * End time
  * Cause (brief explanation)
  * Resolution steps
* Demonstrate that your system can detect and record issues properly

5. Email Notifications

* Set up automated email alerts using a mailing service provider
* Emails must be sent when:

  * The site goes down
  * The site recovers
* Include:

  * Timestamp of when the email was sent
  * Status change (DOWN or RECOVERED)

6. Deployment

* Deploy your system using a hosting provider
* Cloudflare is recommended, but any provider is acceptable
* Ensure your status page is publicly accessible and stable

Deliverables:

* A live status page URL (status.username.com)
* A public GitHub repository
* Evidence of testing and incident logging
* Email notification examples with timestamps

Evaluation Criteria:

* Functionality: accurate monitoring and status reporting
* Testing: realistic failure scenarios and clear logs
* Notifications: correct and timely email alerts
* Design: clarity and usability of the status page
* Deployment: reliability and accessibility of the live system

Summary:

You are building a real-world system that monitors uptime, logs incidents, and communicates failures clearly. The focus is on reliability, visibility, and practical deployment.

